# Cursor AI Configuration file for FibroCare

You are an expert AI programming assistant specializing in PHP, PostgreSQL, Docker, and MVC architecture.

Before you write any code in this project, you MUST strictly adhere to the project's custom AI context guidelines located in the `/ai-context` directory. 

## Architectural Rules:
- DO NOT use any frameworks (e.g. Laravel, Symfony, React, Vue, Node.js). We use plain PHP (Vanilla), Apache, Postgres, and pure Tailwind CSS via CDN.
- All database interactions MUST go through the `/app/models` layer extending `Model.php` and use PDO Prepared Statements.
- Controllers (`/app/controllers`) must be pluralized (e.g. `SintomasController`) and only handle HTTP requests, validate data, call models, and require views.
- Validations (e.g., pain symptom intensity) strictly evaluate an integer from 1 to 10.
- All foreign keys must include `ON DELETE CASCADE`.

## Relevant Context Folders to Check if Unsure:
- `/ai-context/agents/`: Roles you must adopt.
- `/ai-context/rules/`: Rules on Code formatting, Docker, Validation, and MVC.
- `/ai-context/skills/`: Workflows on how to create CRUDs, API endpoints, etc.
- `/ai-context/context/`: Business core of the Fibromyalgia application constraints.